:: Basic Technique {"position":"25,150","size":"100,100"}
<div class="slide-label">Slide 09 of 14</div>

## Basic Soldering Technique

<div class="info-box">**The golden rule: heat the joint, not the solder.** Solder should melt when it touches the hot joint, not when it touches the iron tip.</div>

### Step-by-Step

1. **Flux**: Add flux to the joint.
2. **Heat**: Touch the iron tip to the junction of the lead and pad simultaneously. Wait 1–2 seconds.
3. **Feed solder**: Bring solder to the joint from the opposite side of the iron tip. Let it flow in.
4. **Remove solder**: Once enough solder has flowed, pull the solder wire away.
5. **Remove iron**: Pull the iron away cleanly and smoothly in an upward motion.
6. **Don't move**: Let the joint cool undisturbed for 2–3 seconds. Movement during cooling causes cold joints.

